Comments.Message:
Most of the time I use the Playground for testing, whether a potential bug that I found in my environment, is really a bug. With this scenario it is bad, if errors are not shown clearly and output is generated in all cases. For example, look at...

```
function test(n: number): string {
	return true;
}
var x: goofy = test("");
```

which is full of errors and nevertheless Javascript is generated.
